solutions.content:
Approach is : 

1) Break down paragraph into words. Handled by trim, removal of fullstop,commas etc.
2) Store these words in a hashmap with their frequencies.
3) Store the banned words in a hashset for quick access.
4) Finally check for the words with maximum frequency in the hashmap, and which is not present in our hashset.

```
class Solution {
     public String mostCommonWord(String par, String[] banned) {

        Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        par = par.trim().toLowerCase();
        Set<String> set = new HashSet<>();

        for (String s : banned)
            set.add(s);

        int str= 0;
        for(int i =0; i< par.length();i++){
            if(!Character.isAlphabetic(par.charAt(i))){
                String word = par.substring(str, i);
                str = i+1;
                map.put(word, map.getOrDefault(word,0) + 1);
            }else if(par.length() - 1 == i)
                map.put(par.substring(str, i+1), map.getOrDefault(par.substring(str, i+1),0) + 1);
        }
        map.remove("");
        int max = -1;
        String res = "";
        for(Map.Entry<String, Integer> mp : map.entrySet()){
            if(mp.getValue() > max && !set.contains(mp.getKey())){
                max =mp.getValue();
                res = mp.getKey();
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

