While we haven't reached the destination we need to do the following:
If moving right we will have enough number of combinations (`k <= number of combinations`), then we can go right, else go down

```
class Solution {
    public String kthSmallestPath(int[] destination, int k) {
        int y = destination[0], x = destination[1];
        StringBuilder answer = new StringBuilder();

        while (x != 0 && y != 0) {
            int move = combinations(x + y - 1, y);

            if (k <= move) {
                answer.append('H');
                x--;
            } else {
                answer.append('V');
                k -= move;
                y--;
            }
        }

        while (x != 0) {
            answer.append('H');
            x--;
        }

        while (y != 0) {
            answer.append('V');
            y--;
        }

        return answer.toString();
    }

    private int combinations(int a, int b) {
        long top = 1;
        long bottom = 1;

        for (int i = b + 1; i <= a; i++) {
            top *= i;
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= a - b; i++) {
            bottom *= i;
        }

        return (int) (top / bottom);
    }
}
```

