# Intuition
We iteratively add symbols from the the beggining of the string to its end. What we can do is to think of when the first symbol is "H" and when it is 'V'. In fact if k is "too large" then it's 'V'. In fact too large means it's larger then (n choose h-1) where n is the length of the string and h is the number of "H" in it. So if it's smaller we return 'H' + kthSmallestPath((v,h-1), k). otherwise we insert V and change k: k = k - (n choose h-1)

