# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Calculate a grid of m*n representing the number of possible paths from (x, y) to destination.

Any cell in last colume(can only go down) or last row(can only go right) would be 1
For the rest of the grid, c(x, y) = c(x+1, y) + c(x, y+1), combination of total paths from two cells: the one on the right, and the one beneath it.

starting from cell(0, 0), going right, i.e, moving to (0, 1) means appending an "H", and going down, i.e, moving to (1, 0) means appending a "V". Kth permutation must either falls into these two cases. If grid(0, 1) has larger or equal count than "k", the k-th path must be one of the paths via cell (0, 1).

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(m*n)
m = num of rows
n = num of cols
0 <= rows, cols <= 15

- Space complexity:
O(m*n)
m = num of rows
n = num of cols
0 <= rows, cols <= 15

# Code
```
func kthSmallestPath(destination []int, k int) string {
    rows, cols := destination[0] + 1, destination[1] + 1
    c := make([][]int, rows)
    for i := 0; i < rows; i = i + 1 {
        c[i] = make([]int, cols)
    }
    // last row
    for i := 0; i < cols - 1; i = i + 1 {
        c[rows-1][i] = 1
    }
    // last col
    for i := 0; i < rows - 1; i = i + 1 {
        c[i][cols-1] = 1
    }
    for r := rows - 2; r >= 0; r = r - 1 {
        for cl := cols - 2; cl >= 0; cl = cl - 1 {
            c[r][cl] = c[r][cl+1] + c[r+1][cl]
        }
    }
    ret := ""
    row, col := 0, 0
    slen := destination[0] + destination[1]
    for len(ret) < destination[0] + destination[1] {
        if col == cols - 1 {
            // can only go down
            for len(ret) < slen {
                ret = ret + "V"
            }
            break
        }
        if row == rows - 1 {
            // can only go right
            for len(ret) < slen {
                ret = ret + "H"
            }
            break
        }
        if k <= c[row][col+1] {
            // go horizontal
            ret = ret + "H"
            col = col + 1
        } else {
            k -= c[row][col+1]
            row = row + 1
            ret = ret + "V"
        }
    }
    return ret
}
```

