solutions.content:
while choose V or H for each choice:
eg: for first step choose, group order is like: ```[h...] < [v...] ```
=>we want to know which group the kth is in: first group or second group.
if numH<k,mean should choose [v...] group,k-=numH
so we want to pre-calculate numbers of group with prefix [...]. 
if use combination formula to get C(m,n) for each m,n, cost O(n) to calculate (m*..*m-n+1)/n!,which will cost O(n*m*n) in total.
dp[m][n] is numbers of steps with m row and n cols.
just use dp[m][n]=dp[m][n-1]+dp[m-1][n], which cost O(m*n) in total to dp array.
```
class Solution(object):
    def kthSmallestPath(self, des, k):
        V,H=des[0],des[1]
        dp=[[1]*(H+1) for _ in range(V+1)]
        for i in range(1,V+1):
            for j in range(1,H+1):
                dp[i][j]=dp[i-1][j]+dp[i][j-1]
        res=[]
        while V>0 and H>0:#go until there is only one kind of move. 
            if dp[V][H-1]<k:
                k-=dp[V][H-1]
                res.append('V')
                V-=1
            else:
                res.append('H')
                H-=1
        for _ in range(V):
            res.append('V')
        for _ in range(H):
            res.append('H')
        return ''.join(res)

The main idea is that at every timestep, we need to calculate how many paths we have after we choose "H" .

```

class Solution {
public:
    int CombinationNum(int dx, int dy)
    {
        int all_step = dx + dy, product = 1;
        int start = max(dx, dy), m = min(dx, dy);
        for(int i=start+1, j=1; i<=all_step, j<= m; i++, j++)
        {
            product = product * i / j;
        }
        return product;
    }
    string traverse(vector<int> &destination, int k, int x, int y)
    {
        if(x == destination[0] && y == destination[1]) return "";

        int num = CombinationNum(destination[0] - x , destination[1] - y - 1);
        if(num >= k && y < destination[1])
            return traverse(destination, k, x, y+1) + "H";
        else
            return traverse(destination, k-num, x+1, y) + "V";
    }
    string kthSmallestPath(vector<int>& destination, int k) {
        string ret = traverse(destination, k, 0, 0);
        reverse(ret.begin(), ret.end());
        return ret;
    }
};
