# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Problem Statement says paths to reach from ** source to destination**. These are the keywords of dijkstra algorithm.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Apply dijkastra algorithm along with a modification since with dijkastra we can find the shortest time to reach from source to destination , hence  we have to use an array to keep track of no of ways to reach at every node. Total no of ways to reach from source to destination is sum of all ways it takes to reach destination thate is sum of all ways it takes to reach nodes of its path.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
     O(ElogV)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(|V|+|E|)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    class pair{
        int a,b;
        pair(int a,int b){
            this.a=a;
            this.b=b;
        }
    }
    public int countPaths(int n, int[][] roads) 
    {
        int dist[]=new int[n];
        ArrayList<ArrayList<pair>>adj=new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            adj.add(new ArrayList<>());
        }
//making an adjacency list for undirected graph....
//as if we can reach from A to B via path C 
//then we can also reach from B to A via same path C
        for(int i=0;i<roads.length;i++)
        {
          adj.get(roads[i][1]).add(new pair(roads[i][0],roads[i][2]));
          adj.get(roads[i][0]).add(new pair(roads[i][1],roads[i][2]));
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            dist[i]=Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        }
        dist[0]=0;
        PriorityQueue<pair>q=new PriorityQueue<>((x,y)->x.b-y.b);
        int ways[]=new int[n];
        ways[0]=1;
        q.offer(new pair(0,0));
        while(!q.isEmpty())
        {
            pair t=q.poll();
            for(int i=0;i<adj.get(t.a).size();i++)
            {
               if(dist[adj.get(t.a).get(i).a]>t.b+adj.get(t.a).get(i).b)
               {
                  dist[adj.get(t.a).get(i).a]=t.b+adj.get(t.a).get(i).b;
                  ways[adj.get(t.a).get(i).a]=ways[t.a];
                  q.offer(new pair(adj.get(t.a).get(i).a,dist[adj.get(t.a).get(i).a]));
                }
               else if(dist[adj.get(t.a).get(i).a]==t.b+adj.get(t.a).get(i).b)
               {
                 ways[adj.get(t.a).get(i).a]= (ways[adj.get(t.a).get(i).a]+ways[t.a])%1000000007;
               }
            }
        }
        return ways[n-1]%1000000007;
    }
}
```

