# Intuition
 Anyone getting error on the striver's code from his graph series ,just change the int into long long in the pair<> in the priority queue that stores the distance and take the dist vector (long long) (n,1e18)

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
 Same as dijkstra O(ElogV) 

- Space complexity:
Same as dijkstra + O(n) to store ways vector

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countPaths(int n, vector<vector<int>>& roads) {
        vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n];

        for(auto it : roads){

            adj[it[0]].push_back({it[1] , it[2]});
            adj[it[1]].push_back({it[0] , it[2]});
        }

        priority_queue<pair<long long ,int> , vector<pair<long long,int>> , greater<pair<long long,int>> > pq; //{dist,node} min heap
        vector<long long> dist(n,1e18);
        vector<int> ways(n,0);

        dist[0] = 0;
        ways[0] = 1;

        int mod = (int)1e9+7;

        pq.push({0,0});

        while(!pq.empty()){

            long long dis = pq.top().first;
            int node = pq.top().second;
            pq.pop();

            for(auto it : adj[node]){

                long long  edW = it.second;
                int adjNode = it.first;

                // this is the first time we r coming with this short distance

                if(dis + edW < dist[adjNode]){

                    dist[adjNode] = dis + edW;
                    pq.push({dis + edW , adjNode});
                    ways[adjNode] = ways[node] % mod;
                }
                // if the total dist already stored int dist[] i.e we have reached this node before with the shortest distance
                else if(dis + edW == dist[adjNode]){

                    ways[adjNode] = (ways[adjNode] + ways[node]) % mod;
                }
            }
        }
        return (ways[n-1]) % mod;
    }
};
```

