Use same Dijkastra but with little modification.
we'll use ways[] array to mark the times we visit a node using some other paths but the distance in all paths were same.

# Approach
1. If distance[itr] > wt + prev_wt , simply update the distance array as it is being viisted for first time, and the ways will be ways[itr] = ways[node]: (no of ways to visite prev node.). and finally put the distance and node in the priority queue.
2. If distance[itr] == wt + prev_wt, simply add the ways[node] + ways[itr]. but don't put the distance, and node in priority queue, (time complexity will increase)
